text.tspan: Deaths from earthquakes includes direct deaths from the event plus those from secondary impacts (such as a
tsunami triggered by an earthquake). Due to data availability, reporting and evidence, it's expected that more
recent data will be more complete than the long historical record. A trend in reported estimates therefore doesn't
necessarily reflect the true change over time.
Data source: National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC) of the NOAA
